[{"question":"Or has everything moved to now a debt ceiling debate which will be resolved around that deadline?","answer":"I think it\u0027s more likely now that we\u0027ll have some debt ceiling and some CR conversation.","docId":"131009pmt","qSentId":34,"aSentId":35},{"question":"Is that your understanding of how it went?","answer":"Yes, I think that\u0027s very accurate.","docId":"131009pmt","qSentId":40,"aSentId":41},{"question":"I mean it\u0027s frankly sickening, isn\u0027t it?","answer":"Well, it\u0027s heart-wrenching when a loved one is lost either way.","docId":"131009pmt","qSentId":67,"aSentId":68},{"question":"What were the strategy be from the Republicans to get through this on path that is now causing such havoc to so many Americans?","answer":"Well, we are actually very hopeful that this is actual negotiating time.","docId":"131009pmt","qSentId":92,"aSentId":93},{"question":"Has he misplayed his hand here?","answer":"Look, at first, I\u0027m not going to criticize John Boehner.","docId":"131009pmt","qSentId":113,"aSentId":114},{"question":"Right, but let me ask you in all the eight years that you were the Speaker, were you ever in a position where you even contemplated forcing a government shutdown because you didn\u0027t agree with an established law?","answer":"But look at, we\u0027ve never had -- we never had to do that but, you know, we had ...","docId":"131009pmt","qSentId":130,"aSentId":131},{"question":"Would you have consider it though?","answer":"Well, it depends on what the law was and it depends on what kind of support you had with your -- from your parties.","docId":"131009pmt","qSentId":132,"aSentId":133},{"question":"Under those circumstances could you imagine using that trying to defund that or make it somehow not happen as a stick to shut down the government?","answer":"No.","docId":"131009pmt","qSentId":135,"aSentId":136},{"question":"I don\u0027t think knowing my history of you, you would\u0027ve done?","answer":"Yes, you just made the argument.","docId":"131009pmt","qSentId":137,"aSentId":138},{"question":"Is it 26 as of today now?","answer":"... have died, yeah, as of right now, 26 people died since the shutdown, started.","docId":"131009pmt","qSentId":211,"aSentId":212},{"question":"How do you resolve what seems to be such an implacable divide between these two parties?","answer":"Unfortunately, you know, we talked about this on one of the previous visits when I was here.","docId":"131009pmt","qSentId":250,"aSentId":251},{"question":"Did you see that as the way through all of this?","answer":"I think we\u0027re very close to a deal and that\u0027s one of the reasons Obama is meeting with all the members in both parties of both Houses.","docId":"131009pmt","qSentId":289,"aSentId":290},{"question":"It\u0027s pretty scandalous, isn\u0027t it?","answer":"Well, I think that the Republican Party is beginning not only to look at the polls and see that they are digging themselves a deeper and deeper a hole and of course when you\u0027re digging a deep hole you don\u0027t want to continue to dig.","docId":"131009pmt","qSentId":296,"aSentId":297},{"question":"Does a failure to deal with the debt ceiling on that particular day when it comes up, does that automatically calls America to default?","answer":"No, of course not.","docId":"131009pmt","qSentId":311,"aSentId":312},{"question":"You\u0027re giving Larry Kudlow the last word?","answer":"I have given the Larry Kudlow the last word but the good news is you can come back other -- tomorrow or the next day and have another word.","docId":"131009pmt","qSentId":347,"aSentId":348},{"question":"When you look back to that day, you think back that day and you\u0027ve obviously have to recall it all for your book, did anything at all warned you that he could possibly be capable of this -- the man you knew as you husband and a loving father of anything like this?","answer":"Not at all.","docId":"131009pmt","qSentId":368,"aSentId":369},{"question":"What did you think was happening?","answer":"I really had no idea.","docId":"131009pmt","qSentId":384,"aSentId":385},{"question":"I mean how did you find it?","answer":"You know, in the very first moment that afternoon, I knew that I was faced with two choices.","docId":"131009pmt","qSentId":397,"aSentId":398},{"question":"Have you forgiven Charlie?","answer":"You know, I have.","docId":"131009pmt","qSentId":434,"aSentId":435},{"question":"Did you hate him to start with?","answer":"No.","docId":"131009pmt","qSentId":441,"aSentId":442},{"question":"Do you think it was depression over the loss of your little girl or you think it\u0027s a much more complicated situation?","answer":"No.","docId":"131009pmt","qSentId":454,"aSentId":455},{"question":"Even when you\u0027re described that way, did you worry that\u0027s the rest of your life that\u0027s how you\u0027ll going to be labeled now as the Amish Mass Shooters widow?","answer":"You know it\u0027s a really hard thing for me to see that and have minds months and even years after.","docId":"131009pmt","qSentId":470,"aSentId":471},{"question":"How have you dealt with that?","answer":"ONVILLE: You know I knew that they needed to know all the details of that before they went back to school even that first week.","docId":"131009pmt","qSentId":480,"aSentId":481},{"question":"Did they feel angry towards him for what he did, not just those poor young girls but also to his own family?","answer":"You know I think there are a lot of emotions wrapped up in that.","docId":"131009pmt","qSentId":486,"aSentId":487},{"question":"What goes through your mind?","answer":"Well, it takes me back to that moment and my heart breaks for everyone involved in those situations.","docId":"131009pmt","qSentId":490,"aSentId":491},{"question":"He has -- We had an array of firearms on him, do you think it\u0027s too easy of people who have mental illness to get their hands on killing machines?","answer":"I mean, you know, Charlie had always enjoyed hunting and that was something that he did with his dad and the guns were locked at his parents home in a safe.","docId":"131009pmt","qSentId":494,"aSentId":495},{"question":"You think it\u0027s too easy to get guns that given there were millions of people in America that have a form of mental illness?","answer":"You know I think that it\u0027s hard to keep them out of their hands if that\u0027s so their choice.","docId":"131009pmt","qSentId":498,"aSentId":499},{"question":"You found love again?","answer":"Yeah.","docId":"131009pmt","qSentId":500,"aSentId":501},{"question":"How difficult was it for you to trust a man after what had happened to you?","answer":"You know I knew that if I wanted to have a relationship that was vibrant and alive with my husband Dan that I couldn\u0027t drag the past into my future that there was no future in the past.","docId":"131009pmt","qSentId":503,"aSentId":504},{"question":"ORGAN: Did you ever meet any of the families of the girls in the schools?","answer":"Yes I have.","docId":"131009pmt","qSentId":507,"aSentId":508}]